<paragraph id="8BB7368AD853FFDC3CB4FD0333CDF841" blockId="6.[151,1059,696,807]" pageId="6" pageNumber="965">
D i a g n o s i s: The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D09D853FFDC3DF7FD03306DF9A8" authorityName="Kirsch" authorityYear="1871" box="[468,594,697,718]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Aphelocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D853FFDC3DF7FD03306DF9A8" box="[468,594,697,718]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="965">Aphelocerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
KIRSCH was revised in 2005 (OPITZ 2005). This work included a key to species. The available 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D09D853FFDC3E8CFD6C3185F98D" box="[687,954,726,747]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Aphelocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="965" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sparicapillus">
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D853FFDC3E8CFD6C3185F98D" box="[687,954,726,747]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="965">Aphelocerus sparicapillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimen keys out to 
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D853FFDC3D01FD4E33ECF86F" box="[290,467,756,777]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="965">A. immarginatus</emphasis>
from which the 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D09D853FFDC3EB4FD4E3101F86E" box="[663,830,755,777]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Aphelocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="965" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sparicapillus">
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D853FFDC3EB4FD4E3101F86E" box="[663,830,755,777]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="965">A. sparicapillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimen differs by showing a non-sagittate aedeagus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB7368AD853FFDC3CB4FC8D30EEFF51" blockId="6.[151,1059,822,1079]" pageId="6" pageNumber="965">
D e s c r i p t i o n: Size: Length 5.0 mm; width 2.0 mm. Form: As in 
<figureCitation id="13332A0FD853FFDC3F5CFC8C31EBF82A" box="[895,980,822,844]" captionStart="Figs 266-269" captionStartId="94.[151,191,1506,1528]" captionTargetBox="[152,1060,216,1486]" captionTargetId="figure@94.[152,1060,196,1490]" captionTargetPageId="94" captionText="Figs 266-269: Habitus; (266) Aphelocerus nolus; (267) A. sparicapillus; (268) A. tigra; (269) A. yaguare." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746794" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746794/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="965">Fig. 267</figureCitation>
. Color: Black; row of white setae on the basal region of the sutural margin; elytral disc with two slightly developed white setal patches. Head: Interocular depression and frontal umbo shallow; antenna (
<figureCitation id="13332A0FD853FFDC3D71FC3433B0F8C2" box="[338,399,910,932]" captionStart="Figs 1-27" captionStartId="70.[151,191,1302,1324]" captionTargetBox="[155,1057,207,1268]" captionTargetId="figure@70.[155,1058,207,1283]" captionTargetPageId="70" captionText="Figs 1-27: Antennae; (1) Aphelocerus nodus; (2) A. copanus; (3) A. magnipannus; (4) A. yoro; (5) A. sparicapillus; (6) A. tigra. (7) A. nolus; (8) A. ligulus; (9) Perilypus schusteri; (10) P. apunctus; (11) P. virgulatus; (12) P. izabal; (13) P. alpinus; (14) Cregya fuscomacula; (15) Phonius versus; (16) Pujoliclerus ariquemes; (17) Pelonium falcatum; (18) Pujoliclerus cnecostus; (19) P. trunculus. (20) P. sentus; (21) P. testudinatus; (22) P. catie; (23) P. flavidus; (24) P. convexus; (25) P. meloinus; (26) P. mexicoensis; (27) P. tuxtlas." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746746" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746746/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="965">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
) capitate, funicular antennomeres filiform, progressively shorter and wider towards capitulum, capitulum compact; eyes finely facetted, eye narrower than frons (EW/FW 17/41). Thorax: Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="13332A0FD853FFDC3E55FC7330EAF8B9" box="[630,725,969,991]" captionStart="Figs 101-117" captionStartId="75.[151,191,1477,1499]" captionTargetBox="[152,1030,198,1448]" captionTargetId="figure@75.[152,1030,198,1465]" captionTargetPageId="75" captionText="Figs 101-117: Pronota; (101) Aphelocerus ligulus; (102) A. yoro; (103) Ridica achira; (104) R. merida; (105) Ampleris cacuminis; (106) Plocamocera catalexis; (107) Aphelocerus tigra; (108) A. sparicapillus; (109) A. nolus; (110) A. magnipannus; (111) Pyticeroides desodes; (112) Cregya petalosa; (113) C. livida; (114) C. tobagoensis; (115) C. maura; (116) Pujoliclerus flavidus; (117) Amboakis collucoatis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746756" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746756/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="965">Fig. 108</figureCitation>
) oblong, very finely punctate (PW/PL 75/85); elytral disc with slightly developed anterior and posterior white setal patches, disc with striae of very small setiferous punctures (EL/EW 215/70). Abdomen: Pygidium transverse 
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D853FFDC3D44FB9A3351FF50" bold="true" box="[359,366,1056,1078]" pageId="6" pageNumber="965">/</emphasis>
scutiform; aedeagus as in 
<figureCitation id="13332A0FD853FFDC3E56FB9B30EEFF51" box="[629,721,1057,1079]" captionStart="Figs 201-206" captionStartId="83.[151,191,1264,1286]" captionTargetBox="[153,1059,191,1248]" captionTargetId="figure@83.[153,1059,191,1248]" captionTargetPageId="83" captionText="Figs 201-206: Aedeagi; (201) Aphelocerus copanus; (202) A. ligulus; (203) A. magnipannus; (204) A. nodus; (205) A. nolus; (206) A. sparicapillus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746772" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746772/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="965">Fig. 206.</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
