<paragraph id="8BB7368AD853FFDC3CB4FB3330E6FFF9" blockId="6.[151,729,1161,1183]" box="[151,729,1161,1183]" pageId="6" pageNumber="965">D i s t r i b u t i o n: ThisspeciesisknownfromPeru.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB7368AD853FFDC3CB4FB1533B3FF99" blockId="6.[151,1058,1198,1279]" pageId="6" pageNumber="965">
E t y m o l o g y: The trivial name, 
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D853FFDC3E11FB143089FFA5" box="[562,694,1198,1219]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="965">sparicapillus</emphasis>
, is a Latin compound name that stems from 
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D853FFDC3D31FB763360FF87" box="[274,351,1228,1249]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="965">sparsus</emphasis>
(= few) and 
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D853FFDC3DCBFB713007FF86" box="[488,568,1227,1248]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="965">capillus</emphasis>
(= hair); with reference to the patches of white setae on the elytral disc.
</paragraph>
